<subSubSection id="039B6556FFBFBA4CFF6DFF60FB03EBAA" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph id="4B3E36DDFFBFBA4CFF6DFF60FB03EBAA" blockId="47.[151,1437,151,608]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFF6DFF60FEC1EA92" bold="true" box="[199,300,151,176]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Habitat:</emphasis>
The Baluchistan gerbil was collected from low sandy wadis with considerable salty nature and characterized by rich plant cover of 
<taxonomicName id="8C814D5EFFBFBA4CFD9DFF4AFD0CEAF6" authorityName="in Hazim. Furthermore, Abu Dieyeh" authorityYear="1988" box="[567,737,189,212]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nitrariaceae" genus="Nitraria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="retusa">
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFD9DFF4AFD0CEAF6" box="[567,737,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Nitraria retusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="8C814D5EFFBFBA4CFCA0FF4AFC8AEAF6" box="[778,871,189,212]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tamaricaceae" genus="Tamarix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFCA0FF4AFC8AEAF6" box="[778,871,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Tamarix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. in Hazīm and Azraq. It was found coexisting with either one of the large-sized jirds, 
<taxonomicName id="8C814D5EFFBFBA4CFDF8FF16FD26EADA" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1842" box="[594,715,225,248]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Meriones" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassus">
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFDF8FF16FD26EADA" box="[594,715,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">M. crassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="8C814D5EFFBFBA4CFD5BFF16FC8BEADA" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1919" box="[753,870,223,248]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Meriones" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="libycus">
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFD5BFF16FC8BEADA" box="[753,870,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">M. libycus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This gerbil along with 
<taxonomicName id="8C814D5EFFBFBA4CFBDCFF17FAE6EADA" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1919" box="[1142,1291,223,248]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cheesmani">
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFBDCFF17FAE6EADA" box="[1142,1291,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">G. cheesmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, inhabits the sand dunes of Wādī Ramm mostly around the mud flats, and the salty terrains (Sabkhah) areas in Wādī ‘Araba (
<bibRefCitation id="2F104B2CFFBFBA4CFF34FED0FE2AEB62" box="[158,455,295,320]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refId="ref30180" refString="Abu Baker, M. &amp; Amr, Z. (2003 a) A morphometric and taxonomic revision of the genus Gerbillus in Jordan with notes on its current distribution. Zoologische Abhandlungen (Dresden), 53, 177 - 204." type="journal article">Abu Baker &amp; Amr, 2003a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2F104B2CFFBFBA4CFE66FED0FE36EB62" box="[460,475,295,320]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refId="ref30224" refString="Abu Baker, M. &amp; Amr, Z. (2003 b) Rodent diversity in the Northeastern Desert of Jordan, with special reference on the ecology of Gerbillus cheesmani. (Mammalia: Rodentia). Casopis Narodniho Muzea, Rada prirodovedna, 172 (1 - 4), 141 - 152." type="journal article">b</bibRefCitation>
). Openings of borrows for both 
<taxonomicName id="8C814D5EFFBFBA4CFC95FEDFFC4CEB62" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[831,929,296,320]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nanus">
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFC95FEDFFC4CEB62" box="[831,929,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">G. nanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8C814D5EFFBFBA4CFC7CFEDEFBA2EB62" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1842" box="[982,1103,297,320]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Meriones" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassus">
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFC7CFEDEFBA2EB62" box="[982,1103,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">M. crassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were seen under bushes of 
<taxonomicName id="8C814D5EFFBFBA4CFA28FEDEFD22EB46" authority="in Hazim. Furthermore, Abu Dieyeh (1988)" authorityName="in Hazim. Furthermore, Abu Dieyeh" authorityYear="1988" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nitrariaceae" genus="Nitraria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="retusa">
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFA28FEDEFF31EB46" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">N. retusa</emphasis>
in Hazīm. Furthermore, 
<bibRefCitation id="2F104B2CFFBFBA4CFE5FFEBBFD22EB46" box="[501,719,332,357]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refId="ref30471" refString="Abu Dieyeh, M. H. (1988) The Ecology of some rodents in Wadi Araba with special reference to Acomys cahirinus. M. S. thesis. Jordan University. Amman, 216 pp." type="book">Abu Dieyeh (1988)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
found that burrows of this gerbil were constructed in both hard and loose soil in Wādī ‘Araba. Activity is at its maximum two hours after dusk (Lewis 
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFBCDFE86FB72EBAA" box="[1127,1183,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">et al,</emphasis>
1965).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="039B6556FFBFBA4CFF6DFE63FABDEB8F" box="[199,1360,404,429]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="4B3E36DDFFBFBA4CFF6DFE63FABDEB8F" blockId="47.[151,1437,151,608]" box="[199,1360,404,429]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFF6DFE63FECCEB8F" bold="true" box="[199,289,404,429]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Biology</emphasis>
: Little is known on the biology of the Baluchistan gerbil in Jordan. Litter size ranges from 2–5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="039B6556FFBFBA4CFF6DFE40FBB7E842" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4B3E36DDFFBFBA4CFF6DFE40FBB7E842" blockId="47.[151,1437,151,608]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFF6DFE40FED9EBF2" bold="true" box="[199,308,439,464]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Remarks</emphasis>
: The distribution of 
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFD9AFE4FFD39EBF2" box="[560,724,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">G. n. arabium</emphasis>
is restricted to southern 
<collectingCountry id="3396764DFFBFBA4CFBA8FE40FBBDEBF2" box="[1026,1104,439,464]" name="Jordan" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Jordan</collectingCountry>
. Many reports indicated the presence of this species in Wādī ‘Arabah and ‘Aqabah. 
<taxonomicName id="8C814D5EFFBFBA4CFCEFFE2AFC43EBD6" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[837,942,477,500]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nanus">
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFCEFFE2AFC43EBD6" box="[837,942,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">G. nanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses a 2N=52 and FN=62 (Female specimen). The karyotype consists of 8 submetacentric and 42 acrocentric autosomes. The X is a large submetacentric chromosome (
<bibRefCitation id="2F104B2CFFBFBA4CFE44FDD3FCEFE81E" box="[494,770,548,573]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refId="ref30364" refString="Abu Baker, M., Khalil, A., Sheyab, F. &amp; Amr, Z. (2009) A karyotypic study on rodents of the genus Gerbillus collected from Jordan. Vertebrate Zoology, 59 (1), 111 - 116." type="journal article">
Abu Baker 
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFDD2FDD2FD41E81F" box="[632,684,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">et al</emphasis>
., 2009
</bibRefCitation>
). On the other hand, Qumsiyeh 
<emphasis id="79F5EACFFFBFBA4CFBD6FDD2FB5CE81F" box="[1148,1201,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">et al</emphasis>
. (1986) reported on specimens with 2n=52 and FN=60 collected from Wādī ‘Arabah ‘Aqabah, and Azraq.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
